This paper deals with the estimation of flow characteristics in the Internet, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the mathematical framework for estimating the accuracy of the proposed method, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm for estimating the number of long TCP flows, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of observables to compute statistical information, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method to experimental data, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.PF (Performance).
